  "commentary": "With SPX at 6978 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (14.8B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above 7000 as they're long gamma and need to hedge short deltas. The PIN regime and GEX surge event confirms dealers will provide strong resistance at round number strikes, particularly the 7000-7100 zone where over 21B in positive gamma creates a natural ceiling. Key levels: 7000 acts as immediate resistance where selling pressure intensifies, while 6880 flip level and 6800 negative gamma zone provide downside support where dealers would flip to buying.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get capped around 7000 with choppy action between 6880-7000.",
